{"id":"1909.03770","submitter":"Robert Johnson","authors":"J. Robert Johnson, Imre Leader, Eoin Long","title":"Correlation for permutations","comments":"19 pages, 3 figures. Minor corrections from previous version","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO math.PR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this note we investigate correlation inequalities for `up-sets' of\npermutations, in the spirit of the Harris--Kleitman inequality. We focus on two\nwell-studied partial orders on $S_n$, giving rise to differing notions of\nup-sets. Our first result shows that, under the strong Bruhat order on $S_n$,\nup-sets are positively correlated (in the Harris--Kleitman sense). Thus, for\nexample, for a (uniformly) random permutation $\\pi$, the event that no point is\ndisplaced by more than a fixed distance $d$ and the event that $\\pi$ is the\nproduct of at most $k$ adjacent transpositions are positively correlated. In\ncontrast, under the weak Bruhat order we show that this completely fails:\nsurprisingly, there are two up-sets each of measure $1/2$ whose intersection\nhas arbitrarily small measure.\n  We also prove analogous correlation results for a class of non-uniform\nmeasures, which includes the Mallows measures. Some applications and open\nproblems are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Sep 2019 11:26:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Apr 2020 09:39:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-22"}
